cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with machine learning and specifically with the task of distilling knowledge from a large dataset into a smaller one. The paper uses the MNIST dataset as an example and evaluates the method on multiple datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
